cui_name: Squamous cell carcinoma of the head and neck
reasoning: Reporting cancer incidence. GLOBOCAN 2002/2005 data shows head and neck squamous cell carcinoma at ~6-7 per 100k globally. Squamous cell histology represents ~90% of head and neck cancers.
source: Parkin DM et al. (2005). Global cancer statistics, 2002. CA Cancer J Clin. 55(2):74-108
